---
description: Alembic migrations – creating revisions, not editing applied ones
globs: alembic/**/*.py
alwaysApply: false
---

# Migrations (Alembic)

## Creating a revision

- Use: `make create-migration name=<revision-name>` (creates a new file under `alembic/versions/`).
- Revision file: implement `upgrade()` and `downgrade()` using `op.*` (e.g. `op.create_table`, `op.add_column`). Do not import application models inside upgrade/downgrade; use raw SQLAlchemy types (e.g. `sa.String`, `sa_utils.types.uuid.UUIDType`).

## env.py

- `target_metadata = SQLModel.metadata` so autogenerate can see model definitions. Application models must be imported (or metadata attached) so Alembic can detect tables/columns.

## Rules

- Do **not** edit revision files that have already been applied to any environment. To change the schema, add a **new** revision.
- Use descriptive revision names (e.g. `add_active_on_offers_table`).
